\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 175}, {\"ngram\": \"lighting\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 187}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame alight\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 299}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1996 Atlanta Games\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 325}, {\"ngram\": \"the duty\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1994 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Great Britain took a different approach twelve years ago.\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 435, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999913598, \"rank\": 8.362495635320094e-12, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a different approach\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of a single athlete lighting the flame, seven up-and-coming hopefuls were chosen by veteran British Olympians to perform the honour.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9994404207779393, \"rank\": 0.0005597507884019858, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a single athlete\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 520}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"seven up-and-coming hopefuls\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"the honour\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Renowned figures such as Shirley Robertson, Sir Steve Redgrave, Dame Kelly Holmes and Daley Thompson each selected a representative to carry the torch and ignite the beacon at the opening ceremony - with four young track and field athletes, a sailor, a rower and a young ambassador all chosen.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shirley Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shirley_Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Steve Redgrave\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Redgrave\"}, {\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dame Kelly Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daley Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daley_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Renowned figures\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"a representative\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"the beacon\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 831}, {\"ngram\": \"four young track and field athletes\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"a sailor\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"a rower\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"a young ambassador\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But did these torchbearers go 